com.gliffy.restunit
Class TestNGRestUnit

java.lang.Object
  com.gliffy.restunit.TestNGRestUnit

public abstract class TestNGRestUnit
extends Object

Allows using RESTUnit inside TestNG. To use this, subclass and implement getTests() (you will also need to ensure that setRestUnit(RestUnit) is called). Each will be called by TestNG at runtime, assuming your class is available to TestNG. getTests() is used by getTestsDataProvider() to tell TestNG which tests to run. These tests are run via runTest(RestTest). For example: 

 public class MyTests etends TestNGRestUnit
 {
     public MyTests()
     {
         super();
         setRestUnit(new RestUnit());
         getRestUnit().getExecutor().setHttp(new JavaHttp());
     }

     public Set<RestTest>getTests()
     {
         Set<RestTest> tests = new HashSet<RestTest>();
         tests.add(createSomeTest());
         tests.add(createSomeOtherTest());
         tests.add(createYetAnotherTest());
         return tests;
     }
 }
This will result in three tests being run, one for each of the tests created in getTests.
